---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  path="/privacy"
  title="Privacy Policy — Voxhelm"
  description="How Voxhelm handles your data: minimal collection, on-device screen reading, and no storage of your sessions."
>
  <main class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-5 py-16 sm:px-8 sm:py-24">
    <a href="/" class="text-[13px] font-light uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-white/50 transition-colors hover:text-white">← Back</a>
    <h1 class="font-garamond mt-8 text-4xl font-normal text-white sm:text-5xl">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="mt-3 text-[13px] font-light italic text-white/40">Last updated: June 2026.</p>

    <div class="mt-10 space-y-8 text-[15px] font-light leading-relaxed text-white/70">
      <p>
        Voxhelm ("we", "us") is a voice assistant for Windows. This policy explains what we collect
        and why. We keep data collection to the minimum needed to run the product.
      </p>

      <div>
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-lg font-medium text-white">What runs on your device</h2>
        <p>
          The Voxhelm app and its voice engine run locally on your PC. What's on your screen is read
          on-device to carry out your commands. We do not continuously record or upload your screen
          or microphone.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-lg font-medium text-white">What we receive</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-3">
          <li><strong class="font-medium text-white/90">Account &amp; sign-in:</strong> when you sign in with Google we receive your email and a Google account identifier, used to identify your account and let your subscription follow you across devices.</li>
          <li><strong class="font-medium text-white/90">Billing:</strong> subscriptions are processed by Stripe. We do not store your card details; Stripe does. We keep your subscription status and plan.</li>
          <li><strong class="font-medium text-white/90">Usage metering:</strong> we record the duration of hosted-AI sessions to enforce fair-use limits. We do not store the contents of those sessions on our servers.</li>
          <li><strong class="font-medium text-white/90">Hosted AI calls:</strong> when you use the hosted AI, the necessary request (e.g. text or a screenshot you ask us to look at) is sent to our AI provider to generate a response, then discarded. The provider processes it under their terms.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-lg font-medium text-white">What we don't do</h2>
        <p>We don't sell your data. We don't use your commands to train models. We don't keep your voice or screen content on our servers beyond what's needed to return a single response.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-lg font-medium text-white">Your rights</h2>
        <p>You can cancel your subscription at any time and request deletion of your account data by contacting us. Where applicable (e.g. GDPR), you have rights to access, correct, and delete your personal data.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-lg font-medium text-white">Contact</h2>
        <p>Questions: <a class="text-white underline underline-offset-4" href="mailto:support@voxhelm.de">support@voxhelm.de</a>.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</Base>
